HEADWORD: Isobarism
<hw>I"so*bar*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or
state of being equal in weight, especially in atmospheric pressure.
Also, the theory, method, or application of isobaric science.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isobarometric</ent>⟦br⟧
